,Recommended,266390,30085500,Posted: 21 February,all,Apoc,"It is a fun game that get a bit repetitive but the game is short. A mix of a basic farm sim, restaurant sim and tower defense with a Fruit Ninja minigame and a simple zombie storyline. What you get in about 30 minutes of gameplay is pretty much all there is. You unlock a new crop and recipe around each 30 minutes until you finish the Story Mode in about 6 or 8 hours if you don't waste time. Then there is endless mode and a few pretty vague achievements left for about a 10 hours game so the game's price seems about right and it's a good purchase on sale.An interesting addition but also a flaw to the farm life are the helpers that you need to feed each morning and they will help you on your farm or restaurant. They are very helpful and even a little too much because you will be left with almost nothing to do as soon as you have 2. In story mode you can have 3 and an overkill 4 in endless mode while 1 alone is enough for the restaurant and it require a lot of crops for more than 1 not being enough on the farm. They also won't cut grass or milk cows and the only other thing left for you to do is to barter with the visitors to allow them to enter the restaurant and get their meal.You can and have to enter the forest to get wood and stone a few times for some upgrades but you can't attack those annoying zombies and they will make you drop your resources. Since helpers won't gather those and the few on the farm won't respawn, you are forced to navigate around those zombies and return multiple times. I'm not sure if it's totally a good or bad thing but time stop in the forest so you can't go there while your helpers work to spend some time while they do everything else.The tower defense minigame is actually optional (When starting a new game.) and it's a good thing because it's not that good and actually make you waste some of those crops in the beginning by throwing them at the zombies by hand or with towers. Zombies will steal your crops and break your fences to get there and will give you nothing in return. So they steal your stuff, towers cost some precious resources that could be spent on sprinkler instead and make you waste your hard earned vegetables. It is required for at least an achievement otherwise I would suggest always playing without them.Overall it is a good game with not that many flaws but there are also better games for all types this game try to include."
