,Recommended,266390,10956732,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,inkwat,"If you like farming & cafe simulations in a similar vein to Farmville and Cafe World (minus the social media element), then you'll like this game. It's a lot of fun, and strangely compelling despite its bugs and lack of storyline (the storyline mode is at best a thin sprinkling of plot and really isn't much different to endless mode). The bad news is that, for what basically amounts to a casual sim game with unlockables, the game is woefully short. The story mode is at best 10 hours of play. Endless mode isn't much better, and whilst you can theoretically go on forever, you'll find that you have everything unlocked and nothing to do but hoard very quickly. The achievements are also bugged - several are impossible to get due to not being awarded despite completion in-game (such as the golden scythe). The audio is also irritatingly bugged if your character commits actions (such as chopping wood) off screen, and the A.I. helpers leave something to be desired. I recommend trying this game if you manage to pick it up in a sale, but be forewarned that there's only about 10-20 hours of gameplay in it before there's nothing left to do, and the game has a lot of bugs."
,Recommended,266390,11023947,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,wickdlowki,"Farm for your life.  Zombies, an unexplained event...yeah.  Right down to it, it is a farm, cooking, running simulator.  Farm, harvest, cook, look for resources, and set up a few defenses to stop the zombies.  Not much more to do.Pros:Easy to play.  No learning curve.Graphics are bright, very geared for younger gamers.Its cheap, but i would still buy it on a sale.Cons:Its geared for younger gamers.The control response is shockingly annoyingStory mode is about six hours, it does allow you to play on afterwards, but...After story mode your only real objective is to find the golden tools.The zombies don't hurt you, but they take your resources.Overall, it feels like Sesame Street helped develop it.  Only kept my attention for a few minutes at a time.  Dont get me wrong, it really had a lot of potential, they just gave up.  Only reason i played for so long was because Playfire payed me.Who wants it?People that like farming sims, kids, or the really casual gamer looking for a few minutes to kill.I recommend it simply because of the effort put in to it, and the ease for which a child can play it"
